modules.description: This module provides functions for handling signals, executing shell commands, and managing file operations such as recursive deletion and file search. It works with strings for paths and commands, and uses format strings for error and command execution. Concrete use cases include safely removing directories, locating files in specified paths, and running shell commands with formatted arguments.

Stores and exposes version metadata including the version string, commit hash, and commit date. Works with string and option types to represent version information. Useful for logging, diagnostics, and identifying build-specific details in applications.

The module organizes submodules for handling system signals, executing shell commands, and managing file operations like recursive deletion and path-based file searches. It works with strings, format strings, and option types to represent paths, commands, and version metadata. Use cases include safely removing directories, locating files, running formatted shell commands, and exposing build-specific version details for diagnostics.
